# Consent and Contributor Agreement

This document is the consent agreement signed (or audio-recorded) by every person contributing material to the Orang Laut Heritage Tech Toolkit and the Pulau Brani Project archive. It is paired with a per-item record in catalog_entry_template.md that captures what specifically the person is consenting to for each contribution.

The form is bilingual. Communities and individual contributors should be able to engage in the language they are most comfortable in. Translations into other Singapore community languages can be added as the project grows.

---

## English version

### Who we are

The Pulau Brani Project is a community-led heritage initiative. The Orang Laut Heritage Tech Toolkit is the technical and ethical infrastructure used to care for the memories, stories, photographs, recordings, dialect, recipes, and other heritage materials shared with the project.

### What we are asking

We are asking for your permission to:

1. *Record or receive* the material you wish to share (oral history, photograph, recipe, song, prayer, ritual description, map, dialect word, object photograph, family story, or other heritage material).
2. *Catalog the material* in a community archive, with a record of who contributed it and what it is.
3. *Apply cultural protocols* to the material — including Local Contexts Notices and TK Labels — that tell others how this material may be accessed, shared, and used.
4. *Share the material* within limits you set in this form, which may include sharing with the community, with educators and researchers, with the public, or only with named persons.

### What you keep

- *You remain the cultural authority over what you have shared.* You are not transferring ownership of your story, your knowledge, or your family's heritage. The project is a steward, not an owner.
- *You can change your mind.* You can ask for any material to be restricted, hidden, or removed at any time, for any reason, by contacting the project at [CONTACT EMAIL]. The project will honour your request within thirty days.
- *You can be named or anonymous.* You choose whether your name appears on the material.
- *You can restrict who sees this.* You can decide whether this material is public, community-only, family-only, or restricted by gender, season, or other protocol.

### What we promise

- *Sacred and restricted material stays restricted.* Material you mark as sacred, secret, gender-restricted, or community-only will not be shown to the public, will not be used to train AI systems, and will not appear in AI-generated answers.
- *Attribution stays correct.* We will attribute the material as you ask, and we will correct mistakes when you point them out.
- *No surprise uses.* If we want to use your material in a new way that was not covered by this form, we will ask you again.
- *No commercial use without your say-so.* We do not sell, license, or commercialise contributed material unless you explicitly approve it.

