## Notes for project staff

- *Read it aloud.* Many elders prefer the form to be read aloud and to respond verbally. Audio-recorded verbal consent is valid and should be archived alongside the form.
- *Take your time.* Consent is not a signature collected at the end of an interview. It is a conversation that happens before, during, and after.
- *Re-consent for new uses.* If a new tool, partnership, or surface is added (e.g. a new public exhibition, a new AI feature), revisit consent with the contributor.
- *Document the consent in the catalog entry.* Every item in the archive points to the consent record that authorised its inclusion.
- *Store consent records separately from public-facing metadata* and access-restrict them. They contain personal information.
